Installation
============

If you're using pathogen:
-------------------------

	- Put the includehelper/ directory into your ~/.vim/bundle

Without pathogen:
-------------------------

	- Copy plugin/* to your ~/.vim/plugin directory

Setup
=====

Put the following line somewhere in your ~/.vimrc:

let g:paths = ['/home/foobar/projects/baz','/home/foobar/projects/qux']

More paths can, of course, be added. The script will do the following:

- Set up the "path" variable so you can use 'gf' and C-w f properly.
- Add two commands: OpenIncludePath and InsertIncludeDirective. The former
  prompts for an include file and just opens it (analogous to 'gf', see above),
  the latter will insert a #include <foobar/> directive

The list of paths can be explicitly regenerated with:

RegenerateIncludePaths

It will be regenerated once per application start

vimrc dependencies
==================

Do fully use the supplied vimrc, you need the following additional scripts:

- Conque Shell: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=2771
- Fuzzy Finder: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1984
- l9: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3252
- json: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1945
- fswitch: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=2590
- matchit: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=39
- OpenCL: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3157
- Slang GLSL Syntax: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3155
- GLSL: http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1002
